<h1 class="sectionedit1"><a name="curriculum_2013" id="curriculum_2013">Curriculum 2013</a></h1>
<div class="level1">

</div>
<!-- EDIT1 SECTION "Curriculum 2013" [1-31] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit2"><a name="book" id="book">Book</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
<em>Computers as Components: Principles of Embedded Computer System Design by Marilyn Wolf</em>. The whole book is part of the curriculum. Both second and third editions can be used. 
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT2 SECTION "Book" [32-230] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit3"><a name="exercises" id="exercises">Exercises</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
The exercise documentation and knowledge required to do the exercises is on the curriculum. This includes understanding C and assembly code.
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT3 SECTION "Exercises" [231-395] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit4"><a name="lectures" id="lectures">Lectures</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
The provided lecture slides are part of the curriculum. This includes slides from guest lectures. 
</p>

</div>
<!-- EDIT4 SECTION "Lectures" [396-517] -->
<h2 class="sectionedit5"><a name="recommended_reading" id="recommended_reading">Recommended Reading</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
We recommend buying a book on the C programming language. Our recommendation is <em>Brian W. Kernighan and Dennis M. Ritchie. The C Programming Language. Prentice Hall Software Series, 2nd edition, 1988</em>.
</p>

</div>
